+# Solution: Multiple complex properties of the same ComplexType in IUpdateAdapter.CreateEntry
+
+## Root Cause
+
+`InternalEntityEntry` has a constructor that accepts an `IDictionary<string, object?>` of property
+values and materializes the entity from them. Internally it iterates
+`entityType.GetFlattenedProperties()` and looks up each property by `property.Name` in the
+dictionary.
+
+When an entity has **two or more properties of the same ComplexType** (e.g. `TaxInfoExtended`
+and `TaxInfoExtended2`, both of type `TaxInfoExtended`), the flattened list contains two
+properties named `"CodeExtended"` — one from each complex property. Because both have the same
+`property.Name`, the dictionary lookup finds the same value (or no value) for both, making it
+impossible for callers to supply distinct values.
+
+The same flaw existed in `ShadowValuesFactoryFactory`, which generates the compiled expression
+that populates shadow-property values from the same kind of dictionary.
+
+## Change Description
+
+### `src/EFCore/ChangeTracking/Internal/InternalEntityEntry.cs`
+
+Replaced the direct `values.TryGetValue(property.Name, ...)` lookup with a new helper method
+`TryGetValueFromDictionary` that resolves values in three stages, in order:
+
+1. **Path-qualified key** (preferred, unambiguous): e.g. `"TaxInfoExtended.CodeExtended"` vs
+   `"TaxInfoExtended2.CodeExtended"`. The path is built by walking up the `DeclaringType` chain
+   and prepending each `ComplexProperty.Name`.
+2. **Complex CLR-object extraction**: if the values dictionary holds a CLR object under the root
+   complex-property name (e.g. `"TaxInfoExtended"` → the `TaxInfoExtended` CLR instance), the
+   scalar value is read from that object using the property's compiled getter. This is the format
+   produced by `EntityType.GetSeedData()` and consumed by the InMemory and Cosmos seed-data paths.
+3. **Leaf name fallback**: for backward compatibility with callers that use a simple flat key and
+   have no ambiguity (only one complex property of a given type).
+
+Two private static helper methods were added: `GetPropertyPath` and `TryGetValueFromComplexObject`.
+
+### `src/EFCore/ChangeTracking/Internal/ShadowValuesFactoryFactory.cs`
+
+The compiled expression generated for shadow-property lookup was also using `property.Name`
+directly. Changed `CreateReadShadowValueExpression` to call a new private `GetPropertyPath`
+helper so shadow properties declared on complex types use the same path-qualified key convention.
+
+### `src/EFCore/Update/IUpdateAdapter.cs`
+
+Updated the XML doc comment on `CreateEntry` to document the supported key formats for complex
+type properties.
+
+### `test/EFCore.Tests/ChangeTracking/Internal/InternalComplexEntryTest.cs`
+
+Added two new tests:
+
+* `CreateEntry_with_path_qualified_keys_distinguishes_multiple_complex_properties_of_same_type` —
+  verifies that path-qualified keys (e.g. `"TaxInfoExtended.CodeExtended"`) correctly populate
+  distinct scalar values for two complex properties sharing the same CLR type.
+* `CreateEntry_with_complex_clr_objects_in_dict_populates_complex_type_values` — verifies that
+  CLR objects stored under the complex property name (the `GetSeedData` format) are also correctly
+  decomposed and assigned.
+
+## Files Edited
+
+- `src/EFCore/ChangeTracking/Internal/InternalEntityEntry.cs`
+- `src/EFCore/ChangeTracking/Internal/ShadowValuesFactoryFactory.cs`
+- `src/EFCore/Update/IUpdateAdapter.cs`
+- `test/EFCore.Tests/ChangeTracking/Internal/InternalComplexEntryTest.cs`
